  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Interior Designer",
  "description": "<h4><strong>Job Description</strong></h4>\n<p>We are seeking a creative and talented Interior Designer to join our team in Singapore. The ideal candidate will have a passion for design, a keen eye for detail, and the ability to turn clients' visions into functional and aesthetically pleasing spaces. As an Interior Designer, you will work on a variety of projects, from residential to commercial spaces, and collaborate with clients, architects, and other professionals to bring interior design concepts to life.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Responsibilities:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Work from rough sketches and specifications created by the project manager.</li>\n  <li>Design plans using computer-aided design and drafting (CAD) software.</li>\n  <li>Draft and prepare layout drawings.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with designers, contractors and project managers on projects.</li>\n  <li>Revise drawings and layouts to accommodate changes and enhancements.</li>\n  <li>Knowledgeable to draw for C&amp;S, Mechanical and Electrical works using CAD</li>\n  <li>Manage project site vendors and progress</li>\n  <li>Ensure all works meet quality standards and government regulations</li>\n  <li>Ensure that the expenditure of the projects are kept within budget</li>\n  <li>Attend meetings and liaise with consultants, sub-contractors and any other parties involved in the project</li>\n  <li>Inspect off-site fabrication and on-site installation</li>\n  <li>Ensure that all the defects have been rectified before the arrangement for pre-site inspection</li>\n  <li>Perform any other ad hoc duties</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor's degree or diploma in Interior Design or a related field.</li>\n  <li>Proven experience as an Interior Designer with a strong portfolio showcasing previous projects.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in design software (e.g., AutoCAD, SketchUp, Adobe Creative Suite).</li>\n  <li>Knowledge of building codes, regulations, and construction methods in Singapore.</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.</li>\n  <li>Strong project management and organizational abilities.</li>\n  <li>Attention to detail and a creative mindset.</li>\n</ul>",
